Feature: Async Multi-Device Configuration Test\n\n  Test device configuration across multiple endpoints using async data iteration\n\n  @browser @playwright @device-config @async-driven\n  Scenario: Async Multi-Device Configuration Test\n    Given I open a browser to "${base_url}/${page}/${endpoint_id}"\n    And I take a screenshot named "device_${endpoint_id}_loaded"\n    When I fill the "[role="textbox"][name="Name"]" field with "${device_name}"\n    And I wait for element ".btn.btn-outline:not([disabled])" to appear\n    When I click on element ".btn.btn-outline"\n    And I take a screenshot named "device_${endpoint_id}_configured"\n    Then I verify text with text: ${device_name}, description: Verify device name appears on page\n    Then I verify text with text: ${expected_model}, description: Verify device model is correct